{
  "texts": [
    "The homomorphism Aut(N) ⋉ N → Aut(N) associates to P a principal Aut(N)-bundle P → B with locally constant transition functions, and thus a canonical flat connection with monodromy ρ: π 1 (B) → Aut(N) (which is only well-defined up to conjugation).",
    "Notice that the structure group of M is thus contained in ρ(π 1 (M)) δ ⋉ N L. This twisting homomorphism ρ measures the failure of the above local N-actions (6) to glue up to a global N-action on M. Indeed, if ρ is trivial, then P is isomorphic to the trivial bundle B × Aut(N) with the flat connection corresponding to the trivial connection (cf.",
    "9.2], noticing that trivial holonomy is enough).",
    "Using this isomorphism one can easily construct local trivialisations for P, and hence also for P and M, with transition functions having no Aut(N)-component.",
    "That is, π: M → B is a principal N-bundle.If f: B ′ → B is a smooth map, the pullback bundle f * M → B ′ is again a twisted principal N-bundle, as it shares the same structure group."
  ]
}